1
00:00:07,400 --> 00:00:11,460
♪Just To Meet You, you fell for me♪

2
00:00:11,480 --> 00:00:15,460
♪Just to meet me, into my trap you fell♪

3
00:00:15,460 --> 00:00:19,240
♪Wanna try a breathless love?♪

4
00:00:19,240 --> 00:00:23,490
♪Every move hits the heart, close and sure♪

5
00:00:23,490 --> 00:00:27,460
♪Just To Meet You, you love my playful charm♪

6
00:00:27,460 --> 00:00:31,480
♪Just to meet me,
my romantic little schemes for you♪

7
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:35,170
♪Wanna play another brand-new game?♪

8
00:00:35,170 --> 00:00:40,360
♪Layer by layer, we close the gap♪

9
00:00:40,380 --> 00:00:47,140
=Just To Meet You=

10
00:00:47,200 --> 00:00:48,670
Hurry up and throw all her stuff out.

11
00:00:49,520 --> 00:00:50,360
What a jinx.

12
00:00:51,580 --> 00:00:53,020
(Liu Qin, Jiang Niannian's stepmother)

13
00:00:54,130 --> 00:00:55,000
Jiang Feng!

14
00:00:55,030 --> 00:00:55,880
That little burden isn't dead.

15
00:00:55,880 --> 00:00:57,030
She's back to settle the score.

16
00:01:00,580 --> 00:01:03,100
=Episode 2=
=You're Not Getting Rid of Me Again!=

17
00:01:04,760 --> 00:01:06,230
Xiaodi still is still missing.

18
00:01:06,230 --> 00:01:07,200
None of you are leaving!

19
00:01:08,270 --> 00:01:09,110
Niannian.

20
00:01:09,120 --> 00:01:11,070
- You cursed woman, killed three husbands.
- Let's talk this out.

21
00:01:11,070 --> 00:01:12,560
Good that Jiang Xiaodi went missing,

22
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:14,480
or you'd get him killed someday.

23
00:01:14,870 --> 00:01:16,200
If anything happens to Xiaodi,

24
00:01:16,760 --> 00:01:18,350
I will make you pay!

25
00:01:19,350 --> 00:01:20,350
Jiang Feng.

26
00:01:20,560 --> 00:01:22,480
Jiang Xiaodi is your own son.

27
00:01:22,870 --> 00:01:23,870
He's missing now.

28
00:01:23,870 --> 00:01:24,840
We don't even know if he's alive.

29
00:01:25,070 --> 00:01:25,950
Are you even human?

30
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:28,680
What bad luck

31
00:01:28,680 --> 00:01:30,640
to have such a son.

32
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:31,760
Pitifully,

33
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:34,000
we signed an organ donation agreement
for that burden.

34
00:01:34,510 --> 00:01:35,360
We thought we could

35
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:36,710
get some compensation money,

36
00:01:36,710 --> 00:01:39,350
earn him some "good karma" for his next life.

37
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:46,480
What are you doing?

38
00:01:46,510 --> 00:01:47,350
Put it down.

39
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:48,640
- Put it down, Niannian.
- Put down the knife.

40
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:49,480
(Jiang Feng, Jiang Niannian's Father)
Be good.

41
00:01:49,490 --> 00:01:50,330
Put it down.

42
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:51,840
If anything happens to Xiaodi,

43
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:53,760
I'll kill you!

44
00:01:53,950 --> 00:01:55,320
Niannian, put it down.

45
00:01:55,510 --> 00:01:56,350
Jiang.

46
00:01:59,150 --> 00:02:01,040
Mr. Song, you're finally here.

47
00:02:01,480 --> 00:02:02,350
Don't come any closer.

48
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:07,400
Take her back with you.

49
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:08,360
Do whatever you want.

50
00:02:08,590 --> 00:02:09,470
I'm...

51
00:02:09,520 --> 00:02:10,400
I'm calling the police.

52
00:02:10,630 --> 00:02:11,520
Go ahead.

53
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:14,470
You animals.

54
00:02:16,150 --> 00:02:17,400
Mr. Song, take her away.

55
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:18,240
Take her away.

56
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:20,560
- Take her.
- Got it.

57
00:02:20,570 --> 00:02:21,430
Take her away,

58
00:02:21,430 --> 00:02:22,360
and the debt I owe you

59
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:23,200
is settled.

60
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:24,240
You little brat.

61
00:02:24,870 --> 00:02:25,750
Let go of me!

62
00:02:26,630 --> 00:02:27,690
- Let go.
- Let her go.

63
00:02:50,390 --> 00:02:54,150
♪Chasing through the shadows♪

64
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:58,380
♪We'll still find our castle♪

65
00:02:58,520 --> 00:03:01,730
♪Gonna win the battle♪

66
00:03:05,910 --> 00:03:07,080
Are you hurt?

67
00:03:08,900 --> 00:03:09,750
You...

68
00:03:09,750 --> 00:03:10,710
Why are you here?

69
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:11,960
Don't be scared.

70
00:03:12,750 --> 00:03:13,590
I'm here.

71
00:03:14,430 --> 00:03:15,270
Who are you?

72
00:03:15,590 --> 00:03:16,430
Listen,

73
00:03:16,710 --> 00:03:17,630
this woman

74
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:19,240
is mine today.

75
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:25,030
Gambling debts,

76
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:26,710
identity fraud to open accounts,

77
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:30,310
that's enough to send you both to prison.

78
00:03:30,620 --> 00:03:32,460
(Borrower: Jiang Feng)

79
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:35,400
Who exactly are you?

80
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:36,250
Jiang Niannian.

81
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:38,310
Are you really going
to team up with an outsider

82
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:40,030
to send your own dad to jail?

83
00:03:40,150 --> 00:03:42,150
Jiang Niannian is the one to blame!

84
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:44,280
She seduces rich men with her looks.

85
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:45,520
She killed her husband for money.

86
00:03:46,030 --> 00:03:46,870
Shut up.

87
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:53,590
You better remember this.

88
00:03:55,430 --> 00:03:56,590
She's with me.

89
00:03:57,590 --> 00:03:58,590
(I knew it.)

90
00:03:59,190 --> 00:04:00,400
(Rich boys)

91
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:01,960
(love playing the hero.)

92
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:05,640
Let go of me.

93
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:21,800
Thank you.

94
00:04:31,070 --> 00:04:32,040
Come with me.

95
00:04:32,870 --> 00:04:34,980
I'll take care of all this.

96
00:04:36,950 --> 00:04:37,790
I don't need that.

97
00:04:38,360 --> 00:04:39,430
In this world,

98
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:41,390
I can rely on no one.

99
00:04:43,190 --> 00:04:44,680
Could you please leave my home?

100
00:04:45,070 --> 00:04:47,190
This house has already been mortgaged.

101
00:04:47,190 --> 00:04:48,430
Lock the door.

102
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:53,160
What are you doing?

103
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:55,000
Now let's calculate

104
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:56,190
how much you still owe me.

105
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:57,560
Let go of me.

106
00:04:57,640 --> 00:04:58,510
No.

107
00:04:58,520 --> 00:04:59,410
Let go!

108
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:01,080
You...

109
00:05:04,950 --> 00:05:05,870
Her parents

110
00:05:05,950 --> 00:05:07,680
signed the IOU.

111
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:08,520
I have it.

112
00:05:09,270 --> 00:05:10,310
She has to pay for them.

113
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:11,310
Even at the police station,

114
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:12,560
you'll have to admit it.

115
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:13,640
I will take her with me.

116
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:14,960
How much do you want?

117
00:05:17,270 --> 00:05:18,110
Fine.

118
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:20,040
If you'd hooked up with a rich man earlier,

119
00:05:20,950 --> 00:05:22,430
would your parents have sold the house

120
00:05:22,430 --> 00:05:23,600
and you to pay the debt?

121
00:05:23,920 --> 00:05:25,510
Take your things and get out.

122
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:26,840
Go.

123
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,110
I don't have a home anymore anyway.

124
00:05:37,870 --> 00:05:38,800
Anywhere is the same.

125
00:05:40,190 --> 00:05:41,030
Niannian.

126
00:05:44,390 --> 00:05:45,480
I don't need your pity.

127
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:51,310
I'll give you a home.

128
00:05:51,650 --> 00:05:52,520
Thank you.

129
00:05:52,530 --> 00:05:53,390
Ye Lang.

130
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:54,830
Meeting you

131
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:56,480
is the greatest luck of my life.

132
00:06:02,310 --> 00:06:03,720
(What a sucker.)

133
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:05,480
(He helped me get rid of that trouble)

134
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:07,160
(and brought me big money.)

135
00:06:08,830 --> 00:06:10,390
(What a blessing.)

136
00:06:28,510 --> 00:06:29,750
You know what?

137
00:06:30,870 --> 00:06:32,390
Aside from my mom,

138
00:06:33,270 --> 00:06:35,510
you're the only one this good to me.

139
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:40,600
You're drunk.

140
00:06:42,070 --> 00:06:42,950
I'm not drunk.

141
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:55,240
I know I shouldn't be so impulsive.

142
00:06:58,720 --> 00:07:00,950
But I'm just really happy today.

143
00:07:00,950 --> 00:07:02,430
I just want to drink a little more.

144
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:05,800
You're really drunk.

145
00:07:08,390 --> 00:07:10,310
Where are we going next?

146
00:07:12,870 --> 00:07:13,800
Where do you want to go?

147
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:17,160
As long as I'm with you,

148
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:19,510
I'll go wherever

149
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,190
you take me.

150
00:08:25,390 --> 00:08:26,480
No rush.

151
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:28,600
Go take a shower first.

152
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:30,630
I've prepared a surprise for you.

153
00:08:33,950 --> 00:08:35,700
♪I'm the sun♪

154
00:08:35,700 --> 00:08:37,870
♪Lift me up♪

155
00:08:40,790 --> 00:08:42,620
♪Leave the past♪

156
00:08:42,620 --> 00:08:44,590
♪There to rot♪

157
00:08:45,760 --> 00:08:48,780
♪I'm breaking up all the memories♪

158
00:08:48,780 --> 00:08:51,350
♪Because I am moving on♪

159
00:08:53,280 --> 00:08:54,350
♪But I♪

160
00:08:54,520 --> 00:08:56,000
♪Won't forget♪

161
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:58,160
♪Where I came from♪

162
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:05,200
Really top quality.

163
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:06,200
My money

164
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:07,630
was well spent.

165
00:09:09,270 --> 00:09:10,910
The agent said

166
00:09:11,870 --> 00:09:13,120
you're pretty skilled.

167
00:09:15,990 --> 00:09:16,840
The...

168
00:09:16,840 --> 00:09:17,680
agent?

169
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,240
Yeah.

170
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:20,670
That young lady

171
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,320
said she "checked the goods."

172
00:09:25,480 --> 00:09:27,270
Why so shy now?

173
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:28,480
In a bit,

174
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:30,390
I need you to try harder, okay?

175
00:09:32,870 --> 00:09:34,030
Hey, where'd you go?

176
00:10:04,670 --> 00:10:06,750
(Transfer received: RMB 200,000)
That rich lady looked loaded,

177
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,790
dripping in gold and jewelry.

178
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:11,750
If I weren't rushing to find Xiaodi,

179
00:10:12,550 --> 00:10:14,080
with Ye Lang's looks,

180
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:15,670
I could've sold him for even more.

181
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:23,630
Sorry,

182
00:10:23,630 --> 00:10:24,630
my "dead" husband.

183
00:10:25,360 --> 00:10:27,480
Whether you're truly innocent
or just pretending,

184
00:10:28,270 --> 00:10:30,720
I'm not playing sweet romance
with you anymore.

185
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:35,390
The city's largest business conglomerate,

186
00:10:35,390 --> 00:10:36,240
the Li Group,

187
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:37,630
is holding a press conference today.

188
00:10:37,630 --> 00:10:39,960
This is the first press conference

189
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:41,080
since the death of its president...

190
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:41,970
(Miss Jiang, we've searched the whole city.)

191
00:10:41,970 --> 00:10:43,200
(There's still no sign of your brother.)

192
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:44,040
Keep searching.

193
00:10:44,270 --> 00:10:46,080
I'll transfer the money soon.

194
00:10:51,630 --> 00:10:52,670
Jiang Niannian,

195
00:10:52,790 --> 00:10:53,870
you still dare to come here?

196
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:55,630
You've delayed payments multiple times.

197
00:10:55,630 --> 00:10:57,320
You're already blacklisted by us.

198
00:10:59,910 --> 00:11:00,790
Pay up.

199
00:11:01,440 --> 00:11:02,280
Use my card.

200
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:07,510
This card doesn't even have a number on it.

201
00:11:07,510 --> 00:11:08,550
Trying to fool me again?

202
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,750
Run it and you'll know.

203
00:11:14,630 --> 00:11:15,790
Believe me now?

204
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:18,240
I never default on debts.

205
00:11:30,790 --> 00:11:32,150
You've still been treating my brother

206
00:11:32,150 --> 00:11:33,600
despite all the overdue payments,

207
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:35,840
I really appreciate it.

208
00:11:36,390 --> 00:11:38,240
You should find your brother soon.

209
00:11:38,670 --> 00:11:40,120
He's been missing for days.

210
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:41,750
Given his condition,

211
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:43,000
he may not have much time left.

212
00:11:43,790 --> 00:11:46,510
Try other hospitals or even funeral homes.

213
00:11:46,910 --> 00:11:48,960
Alive or not, you need an answer.

214
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:07,360
(Hacking into the hospital firewall)

215
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:08,510
(will be faster.)

216
00:12:10,220 --> 00:12:11,220
(Manlong City Medical Chain Archive)

217
00:12:11,750 --> 00:12:12,590
(This is it.)

218
00:12:14,860 --> 00:12:16,500
(No Permission)

219
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:20,910
(The Li Group has just integrated
national medical resources,)

220
00:12:20,910 --> 00:12:22,360
(and will establish a connected)

221
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:24,720
(medical archive network
for Manlong residents.)

222
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:27,200
(To enter the national medical market,)

223
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:28,270
(they've prepared everything.)

224
00:12:30,510 --> 00:12:32,000
(As long as I can get into the Li family,)

225
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:33,550
(I can definitely
use the information network)

226
00:12:33,550 --> 00:12:34,390
(to find Xiaodi.)

227
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:39,030
(Breaking news.)

228
00:12:39,030 --> 00:12:41,720
(The late former president
of the Li Group...)

229
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:43,270
(Cracking In Progress)
(Young Master Ye Lang,)

230
00:12:43,270 --> 00:12:46,150
- (showed up at the press conference)
- Ye Lang? Wasn't he dead?

231
00:12:46,150 --> 00:12:49,030
- (An illegitimate son, but highly valued...)
- Oh my, how is he back?

232
00:12:49,030 --> 00:12:50,210
- (He previously faked his death...)
- Mr. Ye, please answer us.

233
00:12:50,210 --> 00:12:51,950
- (Maybe it was internal family conflict...)
- How have you come back from the dead?

234
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:53,840
(Second Young Master Li Hong's bid for power
has failed.)

235
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:55,360
Are you back to fight for the family assets?

236
00:12:55,670 --> 00:12:56,600
Please answer the question.

237
00:12:59,080 --> 00:13:00,270
How could it be him?

238
00:13:19,520 --> 00:13:26,110
♪Stitched-up lips
tear open a blood-red dusk♪

239
00:13:27,920 --> 00:13:34,130
♪You return reborn,
seeing through all my cracks♪

240
00:13:34,680 --> 00:13:41,680
♪This tenderness, a trap or a gift?♪

241
00:13:42,430 --> 00:13:44,900
♪Still, I'd wager my next life on it♪

242
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:49,900
♪Just for a moment to recognize you again♪

243
00:13:49,900 --> 00:13:54,130
♪You are the blazing light in my despair♪

244
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:58,570
♪Lighting the edges of my frozen wings♪

245
00:13:58,620 --> 00:14:02,410
♪I burn myself,
leaping into an illusion of fire♪

246
00:14:02,410 --> 00:14:08,160
♪Breaking free
from dead vines in the ashes♪

247
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:12,480
♪You are the brightest star in the night♪

248
00:14:12,520 --> 00:14:16,340
♪Awakening my dormant fate♪

249
00:14:16,350 --> 00:14:20,840
♪Freeing me from this half-life prison♪

250
00:14:20,870 --> 00:14:25,700
♪As the bells shatter the past♪

251
00:14:26,100 --> 00:14:32,640
♪Life finds its way again♪

